                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 419.11D29/37.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 17, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 313, of
                    February 1 last, reporting your recent action in the matter of your negotiations
                    with the Panaman Government with a view to the investigation of lie case of the
                    riot on July 4 last in which certain Americans were killed and wounded.</p>
                <p>Your action in the matter is approved.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
